WEBVTT

00:03.874 --> 00:07.020
Welcome to the podcast for Pradido Bay Mess at this church.

00:07.220 --> 00:08.322
My name is Dudley.

00:08.362 --> 00:11.688
Today is Monday, March 23rd.

00:12.770 --> 00:18.060
And we are reading Matthew 27, verses one through 14.

00:20.624 --> 00:28.338
When morning came, all the chief priests and the elders of the people took counsel against Jesus to put him to death.

00:29.442 --> 00:34.627
and they bound him and led him away and delivered him over to pilot the governor.

00:35.668 --> 00:52.165
Then when Judas, his betrayer, saw that Jesus was condemned, he changed his mind and brought back the 30 pieces of silver to the chief priests and the elders, saying, I have sinned by betraying innocent blood.

00:52.205 --> 00:54.988
They said, what is that to us?

00:55.649 --> 00:56.690
See to it yourself.

00:57.602 --> 01:00.386
and throwing down the pieces of silver into the temple.

01:00.947 --> 01:04.151
He departed and he went and hanged himself.

01:05.033 --> 01:12.263
But the chief priests taking the pieces of silver said, it is not lawful to put them into the treasury since it is blood money.

01:13.204 --> 01:17.871
So they took counsel and bought with them the potter's field as a burial place for strangers.

01:18.532 --> 01:22.898
Therefore that field has been called the field of blood to this day.

01:23.938 --> 01:35.812
Then was fulfilled what had been spoken by the prophet Jeremiah saying, and they took the 30 pieces of silver, the pieces of him on whom a price had been set by some of the sons of Israel.

01:36.834 --> 01:42.681
And they gave them for the potter's field as the Lord directed me.

01:43.362 --> 01:47.647
Now Jesus stood before the governor and the governor asked him, are you the king of the Jews?

01:48.588 --> 01:50.290
Jesus said, you have said so.

01:51.170 --> 01:55.979
But when he was accused by the chief priests and the elders, he gave no answer.

01:56.881 --> 02:01.610
Then Pilate said to him, do you not hear how many things they testify against you?

02:02.531 --> 02:10.025
But he gave him no answer, not even to a single charge, so that the governor was greatly amazed.

02:11.989 --> 02:14.674
So as we go through this time of the

02:14.914 --> 02:27.587
the payment and Judas regretting and trying to undo what he'd done in his own power and trying to go to someone other than Jesus to undo what he had done.

02:28.167 --> 02:33.973
But they had no power nor any desire to help or to release Jesus.

02:34.393 --> 02:42.962
Now we know that it was prophesied that Jesus would die for our sins and through the death, the burial, the resurrection.

02:43.042 --> 02:46.105
through the power of his blood that we are set free.

02:46.125 --> 02:47.847
So it was going to take place.

02:48.547 --> 02:56.054
There was going to be a sacrifice by the only one whose sacrifice could release us and set us free.

02:56.695 --> 03:12.370
But just on this basic level, I want to encourage you that if you've ever done something and you wish you could undo it, learn a lesson from Judas, you don't go to someone who cannot help you.

03:12.738 --> 03:15.121
You don't go to someone who has no power.

03:15.502 --> 03:18.285
He tried to make payment for himself.

03:18.305 --> 03:20.188
He tried to return the silver.

03:21.209 --> 03:21.790
Couldn't do it.

03:22.291 --> 03:27.798
He wanted to go to the Jewish leaders and to undo what he'd done.

03:27.858 --> 03:28.639
He couldn't do it.

03:29.200 --> 03:42.738
But we know that if we have sinned, when we have done wrong, when we have done something that we cannot undo ourselves, that we always can go to Jesus.

03:42.914 --> 03:50.443
we always can come before Him and we can confess and we can repent, we can apologize, we can pray.

03:50.463 --> 04:03.118
And Jesus, because of the sacrifice, sets us free and we are free to live that beautiful and wonderful life in Christ.

04:04.139 --> 04:09.746
He's said that I have come so that they can have abundant life.

04:10.402 --> 04:14.847
so that they can have a better life than what sin provides.

04:15.328 --> 04:17.010
Sin is just a dead end street.

04:17.510 --> 04:20.734
Sin is a place that leads to destruction.

04:21.135 --> 04:24.959
But Jesus has come and changed everything.

04:24.999 --> 04:29.444
He never sinned, never did anything wrong.

04:29.885 --> 04:33.990
And yet here he is, standing trial, wrongly accused.

04:34.891 --> 04:35.271
You know what?

04:35.632 --> 04:37.714
Sometimes when you follow Jesus,

04:37.922 --> 04:43.551
People are going to think they have you figured out and you might even be wrongly accused.

04:44.492 --> 04:47.797
But when that happens, we're in good company.

04:47.837 --> 04:53.827
We're in the best company ever because Jesus was wrongly accused and did not sin.

04:53.887 --> 04:55.449
He did what he was supposed to do.

04:55.489 --> 05:01.298
He lived the life that the Father sent him here to live.

05:02.050 --> 05:17.147
And we have that same option, as we follow Jesus, as we are transformed by His Word and by His Spirit, we are able to live the kind of life that God would have us live, the kind of life that makes a difference for all of eternity.

05:18.369 --> 05:29.682
Today, as you spend time in prayer, ask God to help us all, to help our church, to help us individually, to be the people that God has called us to be.

05:30.402 --> 05:36.132
You know, there's a scripture that says once you were not a people, but now you're the people of God.

05:37.158 --> 05:38.002
Have a blessed day.

